  "original_title": "\u0db4\u0dbb\u0dd2\u0dc3\u0dbb\u0dba ; \u0dc0\u0dc3\u0dbb \u0dad\u0dd4\u0db1\u0d9a\u0da7 \u0db4\u0dc3\u0dd4 \u0db8\u0dd2\u0db1\u0dca\u0db1\u0dda\u0dbb\u0dd2\u0dba\u0da7 \u0d85\u0dbd\u0dd2 \u0d87\u0dc0\u0dd2\u0dad\u0dca",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "the environment ; After three years, elephants have come to Minneriya",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "After three years in Minneriya National Park, which is considered to be the place where you can see the largest herd of elephants in South Asia, the opportunity to see elephants has come.",
        "Park caretaker Pradeep Kumar told the BBC that a herd of 100-150 elephants can be seen these days.",
        "In the past, elephants had migrated to other areas due to the filling of Minneriya Lake after the release of water from the Moragahakanda Reservoir. As a result, the elephant-human conflict has also increased, the wildlife conservation department said.",
        "However, since the release of water from the Moragahakanda Reservoir has been controlled, after three years tourists have the opportunity to see large herds of elephants."
      ],
